{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":629,"text":"So here's the most important economic fact of our time."},{"time":5917,"text":"We are living in an age of surging income inequality,"},{"time":9947,"text":"particularly between those at the very top"},{"time":12872,"text":"and everyone else."},{"time":14708,"text":"This shift is the most striking in the U.S. and in the U.K.,"},{"time":18730,"text":"but it's a global phenomenon."},{"time":20928,"text":"It's happening in communist China,"},{"time":23251,"text":"in formerly communist Russia,"},{"time":24974,"text":"it's happening in India, in my own native Canada."},{"time":28268,"text":"We're even seeing it in cozy social democracies"},{"time":31235,"text":"like Sweden, Finland and Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34860,"text":"Let me give you a few numbers to place what's happening."},{"time":38771,"text":"In the 1970s, the One Percent"},{"time":41480,"text":"accounted for about 10 percent of the national income"},{"time":45757,"text":"in the United States."},{"time":47521,"text":"Today, their share has more than doubled"},{"time":50830,"text":"to above 20 percent."},{"time":53269,"text":"But what's even more striking"},{"time":55369,"text":"is what's happening at the very tippy top"},{"time":58055,"text":"of the income distribution."},{"time":60297,"text":"The 0.1 percent in the U.S."},{"time":63301,"text":"today account for more than eight percent"},{"time":66530,"text":"of the national income."},{"time":68420,"text":"They are where the One Percent was 30 years ago."},{"time":72913,"text":"Let me give you another number to put that in perspective,"},{"time":75681,"text":"and this is a figure that was calculated in 2005"},{"time":79199,"text":"by Robert Reich,"},{"time":80658,"text":"the Secretary of Labor in the Clinton administration."},{"time":83397,"text":"Reich took the wealth of two admittedly very rich men,"},{"time":88701,"text":"Bill Gates and Warren Buffett,"},{"time":91421,"text":"and he found that it was equivalent to the wealth"},{"time":94370,"text":"of the bottom 40 percent of the U.S. population,"},{"time":99123,"text":"120 million people."},{"time":101965,"text":"Now, as it happens,"},{"time":104329,"text":"Warren Buffett is not only himself a plutocrat,"},{"time":107133,"text":"he is one of the most astute observers of that phenomenon,"},{"time":110860,"text":"and he has his own favorite number."},{"time":114162,"text":"Buffett likes to point out that in 1992,"},{"time":118105,"text":"the combined wealth of the people"},{"time":120267,"text":"on the Forbes 400 list --"},{"time":122596,"text":"and this is the list of the 400 richest Americans --"},{"time":125993,"text":"was 300 billion dollars."},{"time":128765,"text":"Just think about it."},{"time":129966,"text":"You didn't even need to be a billionaire"},{"time":131993,"text":"to get on that list in 1992."},{"time":134966,"text":"Well, today, that figure has more than quintupled"},{"time":138979,"text":"to 1.7 trillion,"},{"time":141865,"text":"and I probably don't need to tell you"},{"time":144043,"text":"that we haven't seen anything similar happen"},{"time":146504,"text":"to the middle class,"},{"time":147889,"text":"whose wealth has stagnated if not actually decreased."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152590,"text":"So we're living in the age of the global plutocracy,"},{"time":156650,"text":"but we've been slow to notice it."},{"time":158691,"text":"One of the reasons, I think,"},{"time":160374,"text":"is a sort of boiled frog phenomenon."},{"time":163352,"text":"Changes which are slow and gradual"},{"time":165915,"text":"can be hard to notice"},{"time":167455,"text":"even if their ultimate impact is quite dramatic."},{"time":170359,"text":"Think about what happened, after all, to the poor frog."},{"time":173591,"text":"But I think there's something else going on."},{"time":176406,"text":"Talking about income inequality,"},{"time":178516,"text":"even if you're not on the Forbes 400 list,"},{"time":181047,"text":"can make us feel uncomfortable."},{"time":183188,"text":"It feels less positive, less optimistic,"},{"time":186633,"text":"to talk about how the pie is sliced"},{"time":189162,"text":"than to think about how to make the pie bigger."},{"time":192214,"text":"And if you do happen to be on the Forbes 400 list,"},{"time":194942,"text":"talking about income distribution,"},{"time":197740,"text":"and inevitably its cousin, income redistribution,"},{"time":201427,"text":"can be downright threatening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203967,"text":"So we're living in the age of surging income inequality,"},{"time":208243,"text":"especially at the top."},{"time":210356,"text":"What's driving it, and what can we do about it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":213944,"text":"One set of causes is political:"},{"time":217610,"text":"lower taxes, deregulation, particularly of financial services,"},{"time":223205,"text":"privatization, weaker legal protections for trade unions,"},{"time":228335,"text":"all of these have contributed"},{"time":230775,"text":"to more and more income going to the very, very top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234892,"text":"A lot of these political factors can be broadly lumped"},{"time":238315,"text":"under the category of \"crony capitalism,\""},{"time":241644,"text":"political changes that benefit a group"},{"time":243821,"text":"of well-connected insiders"},{"time":245983,"text":"but don't actually do much good for the rest of us."},{"time":249521,"text":"In practice, getting rid of crony capitalism"},{"time":252910,"text":"is incredibly difficult."},{"time":254951,"text":"Think of all the years reformers of various stripes"},{"time":258444,"text":"have tried to get rid of corruption in Russia, for instance,"},{"time":261838,"text":"or how hard it is to re-regulate the banks"},{"time":264867,"text":"even after the most profound financial crisis"},{"time":268024,"text":"since the Great Depression,"},{"time":269646,"text":"or even how difficult it is to get the big multinational companies,"},{"time":274242,"text":"including those whose motto might be \"don't do evil,\""},{"time":278253,"text":"to pay taxes at a rate even approaching that"},{"time":281027,"text":"paid by the middle class."},{"time":283135,"text":"But while getting rid of crony capitalism in practice"},{"time":286171,"text":"is really, really hard,"},{"time":288167,"text":"at least intellectually, it's an easy problem."},{"time":291635,"text":"After all, no one is actually in favor of crony capitalism."},{"time":297284,"text":"Indeed, this is one of those rare issues"},{"time":299931,"text":"that unites the left and the right."},{"time":303166,"text":"A critique of crony capitalism is as central"},{"time":305986,"text":"to the Tea Party as it is to Occupy Wall Street."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310283,"text":"But if crony capitalism is, intellectually at least,"},{"time":314621,"text":"the easy part of the problem,"},{"time":316656,"text":"things get trickier when you look at the economic drivers"},{"time":319931,"text":"of surging income inequality."},{"time":322684,"text":"In and of themselves, these aren't too mysterious."},{"time":326423,"text":"Globalization and the technology revolution,"},{"time":329470,"text":"the twin economic transformations"},{"time":332010,"text":"which are changing our lives"},{"time":333708,"text":"and transforming the global economy,"},{"time":335805,"text":"are also powering the rise of the super-rich."},{"time":339272,"text":"Just think about it."},{"time":340852,"text":"For the first time in history,"},{"time":342840,"text":"if you are an energetic entrepreneur"},{"time":345579,"text":"with a brilliant new idea"},{"time":347278,"text":"or a fantastic new product,"},{"time":349693,"text":"you have almost instant, almost frictionless access"},{"time":353372,"text":"to a global market of more than a billion people."},{"time":357352,"text":"As a result, if you are very, very smart"},{"time":361186,"text":"and very, very lucky,"},{"time":362981,"text":"you can get very, very rich"},{"time":365832,"text":"very, very quickly."},{"time":368362,"text":"The latest poster boy for this phenomenon"},{"time":371204,"text":"is David Karp."},{"time":373184,"text":"The 26-year-old founder of Tumblr"},{"time":376039,"text":"recently sold his company to Yahoo"},{"time":378821,"text":"for 1.1 billion dollars."},{"time":381854,"text":"Think about that for a minute:"},{"time":383392,"text":"1.1 billion dollars, 26 years old."},{"time":387806,"text":"It's easiest to see how the technology revolution"},{"time":391253,"text":"and globalization are creating this sort of superstar effect"},{"time":394874,"text":"in highly visible fields,"},{"time":396817,"text":"like sports and entertainment."},{"time":399120,"text":"We can all watch how a fantastic athlete"},{"time":402495,"text":"or a fantastic performer can today leverage his or her skills"},{"time":406839,"text":"across the global economy as never before."},{"time":410507,"text":"But today, that superstar effect"},{"time":412587,"text":"is happening across the entire economy."},{"time":415569,"text":"We have superstar technologists."},{"time":417746,"text":"We have superstar bankers."},{"time":419467,"text":"We have superstar lawyers and superstar architects."},{"time":422803,"text":"There are superstar cooks"},{"time":424232,"text":"and superstar farmers."},{"time":425744,"text":"There are even, and this is my personal favorite example,"},{"time":428527,"text":"superstar dentists,"},{"time":430518,"text":"the most dazzling exemplar of whom"},{"time":432622,"text":"is Bernard Touati, the Frenchman who ministers"},{"time":435984,"text":"to the smiles of fellow superstars"},{"time":438303,"text":"like Russian oligarch Roman Abramovich"},{"time":440984,"text":"or European-born American fashion designer"},{"time":443845,"text":"Diane von Furstenberg."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445890,"text":"But while it's pretty easy to see how globalization"},{"time":448973,"text":"and the technology revolution"},{"time":450885,"text":"are creating this global plutocracy,"},{"time":453356,"text":"what's a lot harder is figuring out what to think about it."},{"time":457523,"text":"And that's because,"},{"time":459049,"text":"in contrast with crony capitalism,"},{"time":461426,"text":"so much of what globalization and the technology revolution"},{"time":465336,"text":"have done is highly positive."},{"time":467699,"text":"Let's start with technology."},{"time":469434,"text":"I love the Internet. I love my mobile devices."},{"time":473044,"text":"I love the fact that they mean that"},{"time":474878,"text":"whoever chooses to will be able to watch this talk"},{"time":478564,"text":"far beyond this auditorium."},{"time":480611,"text":"I'm even more of a fan of globalization."},{"time":483720,"text":"This is the transformation"},{"time":485707,"text":"which has lifted hundreds of millions"},{"time":488131,"text":"of the world's poorest people out of poverty"},{"time":491180,"text":"and into the middle class,"},{"time":492622,"text":"and if you happen to live in the rich part of the world,"},{"time":495664,"text":"it's made many new products affordable --"},{"time":499171,"text":"who do you think built your iPhone? —"},{"time":501697,"text":"and things that we've relied on for a long time much cheaper."},{"time":505519,"text":"Think of your dishwasher or your t-shirt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508143,"text":"So what's not to like?"},{"time":510679,"text":"Well, a few things."},{"time":512571,"text":"One of the things that worries me"},{"time":514675,"text":"is how easily what you might call meritocratic plutocracy"},{"time":518838,"text":"can become crony plutocracy."},{"time":521534,"text":"Imagine you're a brilliant entrepreneur"},{"time":524193,"text":"who has successfully sold that idea or that product"},{"time":527570,"text":"to the global billions"},{"time":528949,"text":"and become a billionaire in the process."},{"time":531515,"text":"It gets tempting at that point"},{"time":533884,"text":"to use your economic nous"},{"time":536859,"text":"to manipulate the rules of the global political economy"},{"time":541131,"text":"in your own favor."},{"time":543217,"text":"And that's no mere hypothetical example."},{"time":545966,"text":"Think about Amazon, Apple, Google, Starbucks."},{"time":550395,"text":"These are among the world's most admired,"},{"time":552499,"text":"most beloved, most innovative companies."},{"time":555045,"text":"They also happen to be particularly adept"},{"time":557969,"text":"at working the international tax system"},{"time":560207,"text":"so as to lower their tax bill very, very significantly."},{"time":564765,"text":"And why stop at just playing the global political"},{"time":569080,"text":"and economic system as it exists"},{"time":571168,"text":"to your own maximum advantage?"},{"time":573313,"text":"Once you have the tremendous economic power"},{"time":577630,"text":"that we're seeing at the very, very top of the income distribution"},{"time":580703,"text":"and the political power that inevitably entails,"},{"time":583953,"text":"it becomes tempting as well"},{"time":586466,"text":"to start trying to change the rules of the game"},{"time":590054,"text":"in your own favor."},{"time":592156,"text":"Again, this is no mere hypothetical."},{"time":594890,"text":"It's what the Russian oligarchs did"},{"time":596825,"text":"in creating the sale-of-the-century privatization"},{"time":600087,"text":"of Russia's natural resources."},{"time":602057,"text":"It's one way of describing what happened"},{"time":603831,"text":"with deregulation of the financial services"},{"time":605866,"text":"in the U.S. and the U.K."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608101,"text":"A second thing that worries me"},{"time":610027,"text":"is how easily meritocratic plutocracy"},{"time":612758,"text":"can become aristocracy."},{"time":615504,"text":"One way of describing the plutocrats"},{"time":617579,"text":"is as alpha geeks,"},{"time":619386,"text":"and they are people who are acutely aware"},{"time":621900,"text":"of how important highly sophisticated"},{"time":624308,"text":"analytical and quantitative skills are in today's economy."},{"time":628490,"text":"That's why they are spending"},{"time":630909,"text":"unprecedented time and resources"},{"time":633686,"text":"educating their own children."},{"time":635583,"text":"The middle class is spending more on schooling too,"},{"time":638850,"text":"but in the global educational arms race"},{"time":641211,"text":"that starts at nursery school"},{"time":642995,"text":"and ends at Harvard, Stanford or MIT,"},{"time":646733,"text":"the 99 percent is increasingly outgunned"},{"time":650211,"text":"by the One Percent."},{"time":651750,"text":"The result is something that economists Alan Krueger"},{"time":654456,"text":"and Miles Corak call the Great Gatsby Curve."},{"time":658161,"text":"As income inequality increases,"},{"time":660964,"text":"social mobility decreases."},{"time":663737,"text":"The plutocracy may be a meritocracy,"},{"time":666495,"text":"but increasingly you have to be born"},{"time":668711,"text":"on the top rung of the ladder to even take part in that race."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673595,"text":"The third thing, and this is what worries me the most,"},{"time":676619,"text":"is the extent to which those same largely positive forces"},{"time":680970,"text":"which are driving the rise of the global plutocracy"},{"time":684160,"text":"also happen to be hollowing out the middle class"},{"time":687592,"text":"in Western industrialized economies."},{"time":690546,"text":"Let's start with technology."},{"time":692633,"text":"Those same forces that are creating billionaires"},{"time":695706,"text":"are also devouring many traditional middle-class jobs."},{"time":699729,"text":"When's the last time you used a travel agent?"},{"time":702668,"text":"And in contrast with the industrial revolution,"},{"time":705749,"text":"the titans of our new economy"},{"time":707905,"text":"aren't creating that many new jobs."},{"time":710707,"text":"At its zenith, G.M. employed hundreds of thousands,"},{"time":714526,"text":"Facebook fewer than 10,000."},{"time":717549,"text":"The same is true of globalization."},{"time":720219,"text":"For all that it is raising hundreds of millions of people"},{"time":723462,"text":"out of poverty in the emerging markets,"},{"time":725802,"text":"it's also outsourcing a lot of jobs"},{"time":728668,"text":"from the developed Western economies."},{"time":730969,"text":"The terrifying reality is"},{"time":733736,"text":"that there is no economic rule"},{"time":735993,"text":"which automatically translates"},{"time":738930,"text":"increased economic growth"},{"time":740633,"text":"into widely shared prosperity."},{"time":742943,"text":"That's shown in what I consider to be"},{"time":745617,"text":"the most scary economic statistic of our time."},{"time":749300,"text":"Since the late 1990s, increases in productivity"},{"time":753358,"text":"have been decoupled from increases"},{"time":756036,"text":"in wages and employment."},{"time":757970,"text":"That means that our countries are getting richer,"},{"time":760914,"text":"our companies are getting more efficient,"},{"time":763538,"text":"but we're not creating more jobs"},{"time":765479,"text":"and we're not paying people, as a whole, more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769350,"text":"One scary conclusion you could draw from all of this"},{"time":773559,"text":"is to worry about structural unemployment."},{"time":777270,"text":"What worries me more is a different nightmare scenario."},{"time":781057,"text":"After all, in a totally free labor market,"},{"time":783649,"text":"we could find jobs for pretty much everyone."},{"time":786851,"text":"The dystopia that worries me"},{"time":788879,"text":"is a universe in which a few geniuses"},{"time":792525,"text":"invent Google and its ilk"},{"time":794605,"text":"and the rest of us are employed giving them massages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799800,"text":"So when I get really depressed about all of this,"},{"time":802433,"text":"I comfort myself in thinking about the Industrial Revolution."},{"time":806262,"text":"After all, for all its grim, satanic mills,"},{"time":810157,"text":"it worked out pretty well, didn't it?"},{"time":812657,"text":"After all, all of us here are richer, healthier, taller --"},{"time":819680,"text":"well, there are a few exceptions —"},{"time":821706,"text":"and live longer than our ancestors in the early 19th century."},{"time":826697,"text":"But it's important to remember"},{"time":829281,"text":"that before we learned how to share the fruits"},{"time":832103,"text":"of the Industrial Revolution"},{"time":833782,"text":"with the broad swathes of society,"},{"time":836345,"text":"we had to go through two depressions,"},{"time":839740,"text":"the Great Depression of the 1930s,"},{"time":841599,"text":"the Long Depression of the 1870s,"},{"time":844453,"text":"two world wars, communist revolutions"},{"time":847620,"text":"in Russia and in China,"},{"time":849699,"text":"and an era of tremendous social"},{"time":852024,"text":"and political upheaval in the West."},{"time":854780,"text":"We also, not coincidentally,"},{"time":857500,"text":"went through an era of tremendous"},{"time":860038,"text":"social and political inventions."},{"time":862617,"text":"We created the modern welfare state."},{"time":864961,"text":"We created public education."},{"time":866703,"text":"We created public health care."},{"time":868407,"text":"We created public pensions."},{"time":870182,"text":"We created unions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872207,"text":"Today, we are living through an era"},{"time":874723,"text":"of economic transformation"},{"time":876684,"text":"comparable in its scale and its scope"},{"time":879990,"text":"to the Industrial Revolution."},{"time":882258,"text":"To be sure that this new economy benefits us all"},{"time":885449,"text":"and not just the plutocrats,"},{"time":887567,"text":"we need to embark on an era"},{"time":889231,"text":"of comparably ambitious social and political change."},{"time":893150,"text":"We need a new New Deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895808,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}